When cross-compiling on x86_64 -> aarch64, libclang reports inner types of
packed bitfield structs (e.g. bch_replicas_padded__bindgen_ty_N) with
align=1, but bindgen bakes in an expected align of 4. The generated layout
assertions then evaluate `1usize - 4usize` at const-eval time and fail
("attempt to compute 1_usize - 4_usize, which would overflow"). Native
aarch64 builds don't hit this because libclang sees host==target alignment.

Disable layout_tests; struct field offsets are still correct, only the
debug-only static assertions are dropped.
---
 bch_bindgen/build.rs | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/bch_bindgen/build.rs b/bch_bindgen/build.rs
--- a/bch_bindgen/build.rs
+++ b/bch_bindgen/build.rs
@@ -376,7 +376,7 @@
         .clang_arg("-fkeep-inline-functions")
         .derive_debug(true)
         .derive_default(true)
-        .layout_tests(true)
+        .layout_tests(false)
         .default_enum_style(bindgen::EnumVariation::Rust {
             non_exhaustive: true,
         })
